BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:MH - Worship
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20081109T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20081109T100000
UID:licqcahh4uq4sp5fse83g10ggk@google.com
DESCRIPTION:Transylvanian Scholar\, Rev. Endre Nagy\nWorship Associate: Jo
 hn Mitchell\n\nRev. Endre Nagy\, Jr. joins a long line of Balázs scholars
 \, Transylvanian Unitarians ministers who are committed to not only improv
 ing the lives of their fellow congregants in their homeland\, but also to 
 sharing with North American Unitarian Universalists the breadth and depth 
 of their passion and caring for their homeland and for our common faith tr
 adition.\nEndre is minister at the Gyergyózentmiklós fellowship and the 
 Csíkszereda church in the Szélyudvarhely District of Transylvania. His f
 ather is also a Unitarian minister. He will be joined by his wife\, Eva Pa
 tko\, a theater director. Endre’s passion is church music. \nHe says tha
 t in addition to his studies at Starr King school\, "I am trying to learn 
 as much as I can about your church music because our church music\, and ou
 r musical life here in Transylvania really needs a "boost"\, and I am sure
  that there is a lot of gold out there in your UU churches\, and in your a
 pproach to music. What I'm trying to explain is\, that I want to collect s
 ongs\, I want to find new ways of implementing music in worship and church
  life. I am hoping to return at the end of my scholarship with a lot of mu
 sical and theoretical material\, which I can than use back here. Translati
 ng and publishing songs\, perhaps organizing tours in our churches with fr
 esh new music which I brought back home with me - this would be the dream\
 , and this is the music of the future."
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalist Church of Davis\, 27074 Patwin Rd\, Davis 
 CA 95616
URL:https://uudavis.org/calendar/
X-SOURCE:UU Davis
END:VEVENT
