BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:LIB - ARE Committee
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20160525T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20160525T210000
UID:7lfn0os1qipa40gksn4bd39s5s@google.com
DESCRIPTION:Adult Religious Exploration Committee\nContact: Kate Raymond\n
 Mission Statement:  The purpose of the Adult Religious Exploration Committ
 ee is to facilitate and collaborate with others to create programs and res
 ources that encourage a free and responsible search for truth and meaning 
 through a variety of formats.\n\n     This committee works to fan the flam
 es of spiritual growth in our church community and to encourage a free and
  responsible search for truth. The ways we are doing this at present inclu
 de providing books for sale at the RE Table\, providing logistical support
  for our Carpe Diem workshop facilitators\, surveying the congregation to 
 assess their needs for religious exploration and then trying to provide ex
 periences to meet those needs.  If you are interested in joining this comm
 ittee to support adult religious programming\, please contact Kate Raymond
  for an application.\n\nARE meets from 7 to 8:30 p.m. on the fourth Thursd
 ay of every month.
LOCATION:UUCD\, 27074 Patwin Rd\, 95616
URL:https://uudavis.org/calendar/
X-SOURCE:UU Davis
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:LIB - ARE: Spirit of Life
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20090106T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20090106T210000
UID:sil21lbqjndqtvq03gg2ctk8cc@google.com
DESCRIPTION:Spirit of Life:\nExploring Spirituality for Unitarian Universa
 lists\nA Tapestry of Faith Program for Adults\n \nBarbara Hamilton-Holway\
 , co-minister of the UU Church of Berkeley\nBarbara Hamilton-Holway’s Sp
 irit of Life program seeks to bring meaning\, beauty\, inclusivity\, and g
 rowth to Unitarian Universalist adults as they deepen their spiritual awar
 eness and connections. The Spirit of Life program taps into one of the cen
 tral functions of religion\, how we—each of us\, in our uniquely constit
 uted beings—recognize\, understand and make sense of that unbidden\, ove
 rwhelming awe at the wonder\, magnificence\, danger\, demand\, and delight
  of being alive.\n\nLed by Director of Lifespan Learning Kate Raymond\, th
 is sharing circle will meet on four Tuesdays:  Jan 6\, Jan 20\, Feb 3\, an
 d Feb 17 from 7 to 9 p.m. in the Library. \n\nThis group is particularly s
 uited for new members who are looking to deepen in their sense of UU commu
 nity and are exploring their own personal sense of spirituality and the sa
 cred moments of their lives.  \n\nNote:  At the end of the course\, there 
 may be an opportunity to continue meeting as a covenant group.
LOCATION:UUCD\, 27074 Patwin Rd\, 95616
URL:https://uudavis.org/calendar/
X-SOURCE:UU Davis
END:VEVENT
