BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:SAN - Improv
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20090104T124500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20090104T144500
UID:6gqu7nlph71droe4ah6jiesqic@google.com
DESCRIPTION:IMPROV!\n \n\n• American Poet Mary Oliver\, when speaking of
  you and me\, said:\n "When it's over I don't want to wonder \nif I have m
 ade of my life something particular\, and real. \nI don't want to find mys
 elf sighing and frightened\, \nor full of argument. \nI don't want to end 
 up simply having visited this world."\n \nThe following class is designed 
 to help with answering the above dilemma.\n \nIMPROV WISDOM\nBased on the 
 book\, Improv Wisdom\, by Stanford Theatre professor\, Patricia Ryan Madso
 n\, this course will provide an opportunity to try something ex citing\, t
 errifying\, exhilarating and life giving – the art of improvisation. We 
 will do this in a friendly\, supportive and affirming way that will engage
  our senses\, intellect and feelings.  We’ll learn to be present to othe
 rs\, to listen\, and to really respond to each moment.  If nothing else\, 
 it will be fun\, and you will talk about it to your friends.  This is a co
 urse especially designed for non-actors.  \n\nThe Improv class runs Jan 4\
 , 11th\, 18th and 25th from 12:30 to 2:30 in the Sanctuary and people shou
 ld bring a bag lunch.  The suggested donation is $50 with no one being tur
 ned away for lack of funds.\n\nThis class is taught by Rev Anne Hoffmann\,
  who studied MBSR at the Medical Center with Jon Kabat-Zinn.  She was the 
 UUCD Campus Ministry Liaison last year and taught very popular MBSR and Im
 prov Wisdom classes.
LOCATION:UUCD\, 27074 Patwin Rd\, 95616
URL:https://uudavis.org/calendar/
X-SOURCE:UU Davis
END:VEVENT
