BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:LIB - ARE: "The Courage to Teach"
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20081022T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20081022T200000
UID:08geqlrh0fpi103v2oq679dsqs@google.com
DESCRIPTION:Teachers\, administrators\, supervisors – All educators!  Yo
 u are invited to join us for a four-part investigation of the critically a
 cclaimed book\, “The Courage to Teach” by Parker J. Palmer.  We will v
 iew portions of a video interview with the author\, engage in discussions 
 based on the book\, and use study guide questions\, metaphors\, and poetry
  to reflect on our own practice as educators\, and ask the central questio
 n\, “Who is the self that teaches?” \n\nWhere:  The Library at UU of D
 avis\nWhen:  6:30-8:00 p.m.\nOctober 22   Introduction  \nNovember 5   The
  Hidden Wholeness  \nNovember 19 Teaching in Community  \nDecember 3   Div
 ided No More  \n\nFacilitated by: Glen Lusebrink: Courage & Renewal facili
 tator\, teacher\, and mentor\, WJUSD\nLonny Villalobos:  BTSA/PAR Coordina
 tor\, teacher\, and mentor\, WJUSD\nSpace is limited.  Please send an e-ma
 il to \nContact glen.lusebrink@wjusd.org to sign up.\n\nCopies of the 10th
  Anniversary Edition (including a CD interview with Parker J. Palmer) are 
 available at local bookstores or at Amazon.com for under $20.00. \n Please
  read the introduction and the first two chapters for our meeting on Octob
 er 22.\n\nAlternate Wednesday evenings October 22\, November 5\, November 
 19\, and December 3.
LOCATION:UUCD 27074 Patwin Rd\, Davis CA 95616
URL:https://uudavis.org/calendar/
X-SOURCE:UU Davis
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:LIB - Listening with an Open Heart Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20081011T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20081011T160000
UID:apfcnf1mgmlqnr0s585q53vnio@google.com
DESCRIPTION:Listening with an Open Heart\nSaturday\, October 11\, 2008\n1:
 00 – 4:00 pm\n \nThe principles and practice of effective and deep liste
 ning can be transformative in your personal and professional relationships
 .  This concise workshop will teach listening skills compiled from our Pas
 toral Associates Program\, from Marshall Rosenberg’s nonviolent communic
 ation\, from Rachel Naomi Remen’s writing\, and informed by our unique U
 U theology.  Led by past and current trained members of our Pastoral Assoc
 iates Program and intern minister Elaine Aaron (sp?)\, this workshop will 
 include time for practicing what is presented in a safe and nurturing envi
 ronment.  The class is also a great opportunity to explore whether the lis
 tening ministry of the PA Program might be a place for you to contribute t
 o our beloved community in the future.\n\nNo fee though freewill offerings
  will be accepted to benefit the work of our church.
LOCATION:UUCD\, 27074 Patwin Rd\, 95616
URL:https://uudavis.org/calendar/
X-SOURCE:UU Davis
END:VEVENT
